Awesome SFDX Plugins: https://github.com/mshanemc/awesome-sfdx-plugins?tab=readme-ov-file

how to login an org using browser:
sf org login web --alias MyOrgAlias --set-default --set-default-dev-hub

how to login using sfdx auth file
sf org login sfdx-url --sfdx-url-file authfiles/Devauthfile.json

to check all orgs authenticated:
sf org list

how to switch between orgs on vs code:
sf config set target-org=MyOrgAlias

how to setup an alias for an org
sf alias set OrgAlias=test-gixs9bvtwceq@example.com (Alias=username)

how to create a new project
sf generate project --name my_sf_project

how to open an org in a browser
sf env open -e OrgAlias

how to see all information about org:
sf org display --target-org test-gixs9bvtwceq@example.com (Alias or Username)
sf org display --verbose --json -o MyOrgAlias
sf org display -o MyOrgAlias --verbose --json >authfile.json (>authfile.json vai criar um arquivo chamado authfile)

how to query via Salesforce CLI:
sf data query --query "SELECT Id, Name FROM Account"

how to query via Salesforce CLI and export to excel file called account.csv
sf data query --query "SELECT Id, Name FROM Account" --result-format csv > accounts.csv

how to check metadata dependecies via query:
sf data query --query "SELECT MetadataComponentName, RefMetadataComponentName, RefMetadataComponentType FROM MetadataComponentDependency WHERE MetadataComponentId = 'Id do componente'" --use-tooling-api

how to create a new sandbox:
sf org create sandbox --name mysandbox --license-type Developer --alias MyDevSandbox --target-org prodOrg --set-default

how to clone a sandbox:
sf org create sandbox --name mysandbox --license-type Developer --alias MyClonedDevSandbox --target-org prodOrg --clone MyDevSandbox

how to create a ScratchOrg:
sf org create scratch --target-dev-hub MyHub --definition-file config/project-scratch-def.json --set-default --duration-days 3 -a <Alias>

how to delete a scratch org
sf org delete scratch --target-org <alias> --no-prompt (para não precisar confirmar a deleção)

check sforce.co/org-shapes to know more about scratch org-shapes.
https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.sfdx_dev.meta/sfdx_dev/sfdx_dev_shape_scratch_def.htm

generate a package for all metadata in our org:
sf project generate manifest --from-org myOrgAlias

to check changes by source-tracking orgs:
sf project retrieve preview

retrieve all metadata from an org, from a package.xml:
sf project retrieve start --manifest package.xml

retrieve specific metadata from an org:
sf project retrieve start --metadata flexipage:FlexiPageApiName

how to setup only users for a new sandbox:
sforce.co/prepare-sandbox

how to setup permission set to the logged user:
sf force user permset assign --perm-set-name PermissionSetName --perm-set-name PermissionSetName2

how to install package (App Exchange) in your Scratch org:
sf package install --package 04t3g000000cCaHAAU --target-org MyOrgAlias

list of metadata not supported on MDAPI (for sandboxes it comes automatically, but for Scratch orgs you need to do it manually or use some tool to automate it)
sforce.co/unsupported-metadata-types
Tools like: Selenium or Puppeteer (tools to write scripts to execute configurations steps automatically)

Easily switch integration and points between production and dev environments 
- To replace strings in your metadata before deployment via CLI (custom metadata and named credentials) you can write custom scripts and automate this entire process (sforce.co/replace-strings-in-metadata) 

tool to populate mock data in scratch ors or sandboxes
sf data upsert bulk --sobject Contact --file files/contacts.csv --external-id Id
- Snowfakery (sforce.co/snowfakery)
- SFDMU (help.sfdmu.com/get-started / sforce.co/sfdmu)
- texei (https://texei.com/en/advices/easily-load-data-into-your-scratch-org-or-sandbox-part-1/)